channel.title: Wont run?
channel.description: OK I got a new computer and I wan't to run my server. I have it portforwarded and everything from my old computer. I have IP duc and I have tried turning off my firewall, yet no one can connect...any Ideas why?

item.title: Wont run?
item.dc:creator: @Amerks5 Amerks5
item.description:
@Amerks5 wrote:

[quote=“Kyle11594, post:21, topic:169447”]Is your no-ip set up? If it is, it is running? If it is. Is your server running? If it is…

If you get a new computer… You need to make sure you port forwarded it to the right computer.
You dont port forward for 2 computers the same way.

Hit start>run>cmd>ipconfig

That will give you a screen that tells you a bunch of stuff.

One of the things should say something like…

192.168.1.100
or
192.168.1.101
192.168.1.102
192.168.1.103

one of those…
Thats the one you have to port forward… same thing happened to me just the other day…

oh and another thing.
After you port forward. If you have a new computer you need to make a new DNS host on your computer. Or else nobody else can access it.[/quote]

A DNS host?

First go to Start, click on Network, at the top click “Network and Sharing Center”.

Another screen will pop up, and at the very bottom on the left side, there is something Called “Windows Firewall”, Click it.

Another screen will pop up, and click “Change Settings”, and another screen will pop up, Click the “Exceptions” bar, and from here, Follow this guide:
